📊 Statistical Analysis of Poverty in West Java, 2022
Overview:
This project presents a statistical analysis of poverty data across regencies and cities in West Java Province in 2022 using official data published by Statistics Indonesia (BPS). The analysis aims to understand regional poverty conditions, measure the number of poor residents, calculate poverty proportions, and examine variations in poverty levels through descriptive statistical methods.
The project provides valuable insights into socioeconomic disparities among regions and demonstrates how statistical techniques can be applied to analyze public-sector data effectively.

Objectives:
Analyze poverty conditions across regencies and cities in West Java.
Measure the distribution of poor populations among regions.
Calculate descriptive statistical measures such as mean and variance.
Examine regional disparities in poverty levels.
Interpret statistical findings to better understand socioeconomic conditions.

