Key Findings:
The average number of poor residents in West Java in 2022 was 13.66 thousand people.
The variance (S²) was 105.21, indicating noticeable variation among regions.
Bogor Regency recorded the highest number of poor residents with 36.70 thousand people.
Banjar City recorded the lowest number of poor residents with 0.86 thousand people.
The analysis highlights significant socioeconomic differences among regencies and cities across West Java.

